{"type":"message","id":"cd0ca694","parentId":"06982aea","timestamp":"2026-03-15T10:34:54.586Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"867cb5ed-980d-403d-a3ef-5de140125e85","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"=================================================================\n学术搜索结果: speech synthesis duration control prosody naturalness\n=================================================================\n数据源统计: {'arXiv': 0, 'OpenAlex': 8, 'Crossref': 8}\n去重后共 16 篇\n\n[1] [OpenAlex] (2023) A high-performance neuroprosthesis for speech decoding and avatar control\n     作者: Sean L. Metzger, Kaylo T. Littlejohn, Alexander B. Silva et al.\n     被引 422  |  https://doi.org/10.1038/s41586-023-06443-4\n\n[2] [OpenAlex] (2024) Enriching Location Representation with Detailed Semantic Information\n     作者: Mohamed Ettaleb, Mouna Kamel\n     被引 317  |  http://arxiv.org/abs/2407.21783\n     摘要: Cyber-physical systems (CPS) are critical to modern infrastructure, but are vulnerable to faults and anomalies that threaten their operational safety. In this work, we evaluate the...\n     PDF: https://arxiv.org/pdf/2407.21783\n\n[3] [OpenAlex] (2023) Neural Codec Language Models are Zero-Shot Text to Speech Synthesizers\n     作者: Chengyi Wang, Sanyuan Chen, Yu Wu et al.\n     被引 161  |  http://arxiv.org/abs/2301.02111\n     摘要: We introduce a language modeling approach for text to speech synthesis (TTS). Specifically, we train a neural codec language model (called Vall-E) using discrete codes derived from...\n     PDF: https://arxiv.org/pdf/2301.02111\n\n[4] [OpenAlex] (2023) Recent advancements in multimodal human–robot interaction\n     作者: Hang Su, Wen Qi, Jiahao Chen et al.\n     被引 141  |  https://doi.org/10.3389/fnbot.2023.1084000\n     摘要: Robotics have advanced significantly over the years, and human-robot interaction (HRI) is now playing an important role in delivering the best user experience, cutting down on labo...\n     PDF: https://www.frontiersin.org/articles/10.3389/fnbot.2023.1084000/pdf\n\n[5] [OpenAlex] (2023) Speak, Read and Prompt: High-Fidelity Text-to-Speech with Minimal Supervision\n     作者: Eugene Kharitonov, Damien Vincent, Zalán Borsos et al.\n     被引 85  |  https://doi.org/10.1162/tacl_a_00618\n     摘要: Abstract We introduce SPEAR-TTS, a multi-speaker text-to-speech (TTS) system that can be trained with minimal supervision. By combining two types of discrete speech representations...\n     PDF: https://direct.mit.edu/tacl/article-pdf/doi/10.1162/tacl_a_00618/2200655/tacl_a_00618.pdf\n\n[6] [OpenAlex] (2023) An Overview of Affective Speech Synthesis and Conversion in the Deep Learning Era\n     作者: Andreas Triantafyllopoulos, Björn W. Schuller, Gökçe İymen et al.\n     被引 68  |  https://doi.org/10.1109/jproc.2023.3250266\n     摘要: Speech is the fundamental mode of human communication, and its synthesis has long been a core priority in human–computer interaction research. In recent years, machines have manage...\n\n[7] [OpenAlex] (2023) NaturalSpeech 2: Latent Diffusion Models are Natural and Zero-Shot Speech and Singing Synthesizers\n     作者: Kai Shen, Zeqian Ju, Xu Tan et al.\n     被引 37  |  http://arxiv.org/abs/2304.09116\n     摘要: Scaling text-to-speech (TTS) to large-scale, multi-speaker, and in-the-wild datasets is important to capture the diversity in human speech such as speaker identities, prosodies, an...\n     PDF: https://arxiv.org/pdf/2304.09116\n\n[8] [OpenAlex] (2024) Deep learning-based expressive speech synthesis: a systematic review of approaches, challenges, and resources\n     作者: Huda Mohammed Barakat, Oytun Türk, Cenk Demiroğlu\n     被引 35  |  https://doi.org/10.1186/s13636-024-00329-7\n     摘要: Abstract Speech synthesis has made significant strides thanks to the transition from machine learning to deep learning models. Contemporary text-to-speech (TTS) models possess the ...\n     PDF: https://asmp-eurasipjournals.springeropen.com/counter/pdf/10.1186/s13636-024-00329-7\n\n[9] [Cros